Kaduna Electric said that arrangement has been concluded for the roll out of meters to its customers under the Meter Asset Provider (MAP) Scheme. A statement by the company’s Head of Corporate Communication, Abdulazeez Abdullahi, said from Monday, August 5, customers can now apply for meters under the scheme, saying, the Nigerian Electricity Regulatory Commission had approved 4 meter providers under the scheme for Kaduna Electric namely; Integrated Power Limited, Holley Engineering Limited, Mojec International Limited and Cresthill Limited. The statement said Holley Engineering Limited, Cresthill and Mojec shall provide meters for customers in Kaduna while Integrated Power shall service customers in Sokoto, Kebbi and Zamfara states. Kaduna Electric in the statement reveals that customers wishing to be metered can indicate interest by visiting the company’s website at www.kadunaelectric.com <http://www.kadunaelectric.com> and fill the MAP meter request form to kick start the installation process, “upon filling the form, an assessment of the customer’s  property shall be conducted to determine the suitable meter to be installed after which the customer is expected to pay for the meter.” The statement assured that installation is to be done within 10 days, adding that in preparation towards the commencement of the MAP scheme, a series of enlightenment sessions have been held to educate customers on how to access the scheme. The company appeals to its customers to embrace the scheme and get metered and warned consumers to desist from fraudulent acts such as meter bypass and tampering to make the scheme a success.  Ikeja Electric rolls out prepaid meters for Ikorodu customers Mojec partners banks, to roll out pre-paid meters Ikeja Electric, Mojec sign N570m  transformers, meters deal Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of you